11 B. A charitable alcoholic beverage event shall be conducted
12 solely to raise funds for charitable purposes. A charitable
13 alcoholic beverage license shall allow the event attendees access to
14 tastings, samples, dinners and alcoholic beverages as parts part of
15 their entrance fee or ticket price. Wine, spirits and/or beer used
16 in, served or consumed at a charitable alcoholic beverage event may
17 be purchased by the charitable organization or donated by any person
18 or entity.
19 C. The charitable alcoholic beverage event license shall be
20 issued for a period not exceeding four (4) days. Only eight such
21 licenses may be issued to an organization in any twelve-month
22 period; provided, institutions of higher education in this state
23 shall not be restricted to the maximum number of event licenses
24 issued in any twelve-month period pursuant to this subsection. The
